    "note": "Scores were tuned for a fully customizable 9-hour Jeju private charter format. Comfort, mobility-friendliness, family fit, and senior fit score very high because the private format eliminates group constraints and the driver-guide handles all transit. Same-day-flight fit scores 4 because Jeju Airport is centrally located and the driver-guide can flex the route around flight times. Walking and culture levels are weighted averages across the three recommended routes; the on-the-day load can move significantly depending on the chosen route.",
    "duration_hours": 9,
    "stop_count": 4,
    "score_rationale": {
      "private_fit": "Direct match: this is a per-vehicle private charter.",
      "mobility_friendly_fit": "Door-to-door private vehicle eliminates most public-transport mobility friction; only Seongsan summit and Cheonjiyeon stairs reduce friendliness for those specific stops.",
      "young_kids_fit": "Best-in-class for kids because pacing, snack stops, and route choice are all adjustable.",
      "weather_sensitivity": "Low because the driver-guide can shift toward indoor stops (Manjanggul, Hallim caves, O'sulloc, Yakcheonsa) on bad-weather days.",
      "value_for_money_fit": "Mid: per-vehicle pricing is excellent value for groups of 4 to 9 but expensive for solo travelers.",
      "iconic_landmark_fit": "Maxed because the route can include Seongsan, Manjanggul, Cheonjiyeon, and Jusangjeolli in any combination.",
      "same_day_flight_fit": "Above average because Jeju Airport is central and the driver-guide can drop off there at the end of the 9 hours."
